  "A researcher claims the mean commute time in a city is less than 30 minutes. She surveys 50 workers and finds x-bar = 27.4 with s = 8.2. On the AP exam, which is the correct set of hypotheses?": "",
  "H₀: μ = 27.4, Hₐ: μ ≠ 27.4": "",
  "H₀: μ = 30, Hₐ: μ < 30": "",
  "H₀: μ < 30, Hₐ: μ = 30": "",
  "H₀: x-bar = 30, Hₐ: x-bar < 30": "",
  "Hypotheses are about the population parameter μ, not the sample statistic. H₀ states the null value and Hₐ reflects the research claim (less than 30).": "",
  "On a free-response question, a student performs a one-proportion z-test for a coin she suspects is unfair. She flips it 100 times and gets 62 heads. Which condition check is she most likely to forget?": "",
  "Verifying np₀ ≥ 10 and n(1−p₀) ≥ 10": "",
  "Concluding in context by referring to the specific coin and the claim about fairness": "",
  "The 10% condition (independence): 100 flips is less than 10% of all possible flips": "",
  "Stating that the coin was flipped randomly": "",
  "The most commonly missed step on AP exams is interpreting the result in the specific context of the problem rather than giving a generic statistical conclusion.": "",
